** Question 2:

In the original listing 3-2, the queue has a large capacity. If the consumer task ("press_task") ever fails to keep up with
the producer tasks, the queue could fill up. Listing 3-3 addresses this by ensuring that if a "button release" event cannot
be queued, the system forces a "fail-safe" state. It prioritizes clearing the system state over processing old button 
presses, ensuring the "press" (LED) deactivates immediately if the software loses track of button states. The changes made 
to implement this were the queue size, a new constant, producer logic (debounce_task), and consumer logic (press_task).

