Both GPIO_LED1 and GPIO_LED2 are intitialized to HIGH in the setup() function before the tasks are started. Once the tasks begin execution,
GPIO_LED1 and GPIO_LED2 will attempt to blink nearly simultaneously because both tasks are created with the same priority (1) and pinned 
to the same CPU core. The "delay" in this program refers to the timing drift or interval between blinks, which occurs for different reasons
in each task such as a cummulative delay in Task1, a precise interval in Task2, and artificial processing delay.
